[
  {
    "type": "section",
    "label": "DUELO",
    "es": "",
    "tr": ""
  },
  {
    "es": "Como cualquier atardecer,",
    "tr": "Like any sunset,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Salió a caminar.",
    "tr": "He went out for a walk."
  },
  {
    "es": "Tranquilo el pueblo,",
    "tr": "The town was calm,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Sin sopeschar.",
    "tr": "Without suspecting anything."
  },
  {
    "es": "Perdido en sombras,",
    "tr": "Lost in shadows,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Un cuerpo ajeno,",
    "tr": "An unknown body,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Sintio cruzar.",
    "tr": "Felt crossing by."
  },
  {
    "es": "El aire se hizo espeso",
    "tr": "The air grew heavy,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Susurros de hierro",
    "tr": "Whispers of iron,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Rabia y miedo adentro",
    "tr": "Rage and fear inside,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Confusión de viento",
    "tr": "Confusion of wind,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Noche de tormento",
    "tr": "Night of torment,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Gritos rompen el silencio",
    "tr": "Cries break the silence."
  },
  {
    "es": "Pregunta",
    "tr": "A question,"
  },
  {
    "es": "sin voz ni cielo",
    "tr": "Without voice nor sky,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Herido el tiempo",
    "tr": "Time wounded,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Sigue su duelo",
    "tr": "Continues its mourning."
  },
  {
    "es": "Sale el sol",
    "tr": "The sun rises,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Aunque más lento",
    "tr": "Though slower,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Duele pero",
    "tr": "It hurts, but"
  },
  {
    "es": "Queda aliento.",
    "tr": "Breath remains."
  },
  {
    "es": "La vida no",
    "tr": "Life doesn’t"
  },
  {
    "es": "Busca entender,",
    "tr": "Seek to understand,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Bajo la herida",
    "tr": "Under the wound,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Renace la piel.",
    "tr": "The skin is reborn."
  },
  {
    "type": "section",
    "label": "LUZ Y SAL",
    "es": "",
    "tr": ""
  },
  {
    "es": "Amanece en el mar",
    "tr": "Dawn breaks over the sea,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Brisas de vida y sal",
    "tr": "Breezes of life and salt,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Su vaivén recuerda al pasar",
    "tr": "Its sway reminds as it passes,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Que todo vuelve a cambiar",
    "tr": "That everything changes again."
  },
  {
    "es": "La historia viene y va,",
    "tr": "The story comes and goes,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Con risas y pesar.",
    "tr": "With laughter and sorrow."
  },
  {
    "es": "Luz y sal.",
    "tr": "Light and salt."
  },
  {
    "es": "Lo nuestro fue Luz y sal",
    "tr": "Ours was light and salt,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Nacer dulce, e intenso al andar",
    "tr": "Born sweet, and intense as we walked,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Mareas, lluvias y sol",
    "tr": "Tides, rains, and sun,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Sin rumbo, siguiendo al corazón",
    "tr": "Without direction, following the heart."
  },
  {
    "es": "El viento quise atar",
    "tr": "I tried to tie the wind,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Guardar tu risa en un cajón",
    "tr": "Keep your laughter in a drawer,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Pero el tiempo en su canción",
    "tr": "But time in its song,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Al mar te devolvió.",
    "tr": "Returned you to the sea."
  },
  {
    "es": "En la orilla me dejó",
    "tr": "On the shore it left me,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Luz y sal.",
    "tr": "Light and salt."
  },
  {
    "es": "Amanece en el mar",
    "tr": "Dawn breaks over the sea."
  },
  {
    "type": "section",
    "label": "PIMIENTO",
    "es": "",
    "tr": ""
  },
  {
    "es": "Viejo pimiento,",
    "tr": "Old pepper tree,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Hoy vuelvo a visitarte",
    "tr": "Today I come to visit you again,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Dicen que sabes",
    "tr": "They say you know"
  },
  {
    "es": "tratar males de poetas.",
    "tr": "How to heal poets’ troubles."
  },
  {
    "es": "Con el corazón afuera nací,",
    "tr": "I was born with my heart exposed,"
  },
  {
    "es": "desde niño quiere más que latir.",
    "tr": "Since childhood it has wanted more than to beat."
  },
  {
    "es": "No quiere que yo le cuente del mundo,",
    "tr": "It doesn’t want me to tell it about the world,"
  },
  {
    "es": "por sí mismo él lo quiere sentir.",
    "tr": "It wants to feel it for itself."
  },
  {
    "es": "Viejo pimiento,",
    "tr": "Old pepper tree,"
  },
  {
    "es": "mi refugio y mi lugar.",
    "tr": "My refuge and my place."
  },
  {
    "es": "Desnudo el corazón,",
    "tr": "Naked heart,"
  },
  {
    "es": "todo lo atraviesa:",
    "tr": "It feels everything:"
  },
  {
    "es": "Farol en tormentas,",
    "tr": "Lantern in storms,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Pero se quiebra con un mirar.",
    "tr": "But it breaks with a glance."
  },
  {
    "es": "Ama rápido, sin medida va.",
    "tr": "It loves fast, without measure."
  },
  {
    "es": "Encuentra belleza en lo sencillo.",
    "tr": "It finds beauty in the simple."
  },
  {
    "es": "Pero en su sangre carga con penas ajenas,",
    "tr": "But in its blood it carries others’ sorrows,"
  },
  {
    "es": "y se funde.",
    "tr": "And melts away."
  },
  {
    "es": "Si a quedarse afuera insiste,",
    "tr": "If it insists on staying outside,"
  },
  {
    "es": "En tu sombra déjalo latir.",
    "tr": "Let it beat in your shade."
  },
  {
    "es": "Viejo pimiento,",
    "tr": "Old pepper tree,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Fuiste el juego en mi infancia.",
    "tr": "You were the game of my childhood."
  },
  {
    "es": "Me cubro con tus hojas",
    "tr": "I cover myself with your leaves"
  },
  {
    "es": "pa volver a nacer.",
    "tr": "To be born again."
  },
  {
    "type": "section",
    "label": "PASO",
    "es": "",
    "tr": ""
  },
  {
    "es": "Una voz, una oración final.",
    "tr": "A voice, a final prayer."
  },
  {
    "es": "Un adiós, un “te amo papá”.",
    "tr": "A farewell, an \"I love you, dad.\""
  },
  {
    "es": "Tú me miras pensando en lo que vendrá.",
    "tr": "You look at me thinking about what will come."
  },
  {
    "es": "¿Qué pasa cuando la vida se va?",
    "tr": "What happens when life goes away?"
  },
  {
    "es": "Tal vez se detiene el tiempo,",
    "tr": "Perhaps time stops,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Tal vez vuelve a empezar,",
    "tr": "Perhaps it starts again,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Tal vez esta vida es un sueño,",
    "tr": "Perhaps this life is a dream,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Del cual despiertas en paz.",
    "tr": "From which you awaken in peace."
  },
  {
    "es": "Y cuando despiertes con la nueva luz.",
    "tr": "And when you wake with the new light,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Sin nombre ni el cuerpo que fuiste tú,",
    "tr": "Without the name or body that you were,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Y en una memoria brote nuestra historia,",
    "tr": "And in a memory our story blossoms,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Mírame, sonríe, sigo en ti.",
    "tr": "Look at me, smile, I’m still in you."
  },
  {
    "es": "Este último río no se cruza a fuerza,",
    "tr": "This final river is not crossed by force,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Ni razón, ni sentidos nos pueden guiar.",
    "tr": "Neither reason nor senses can guide us."
  },
  {
    "es": "Deja fluir, sin mirar atrás",
    "tr": "Let it flow, without looking back,"
  },
  {
    "es": "El río sabe a dónde va.",
    "tr": "The river knows where it’s going."
  },
  {
    "type": "section",
    "label": "VIDAS",
    "es": "",
    "tr": ""
  },
  {
    "es": "Cielo gris en nuestro hogar,",
    "tr": "Gray sky in our home,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Tú ya en el mar.",
    "tr": "You already in the sea."
  },
  {
    "es": "Polvo el cuerpo,",
    "tr": "Dust the body,"
  },
  {
    "es": "Nunca sabrá.",
    "tr": "It will never know."
  },
  {
    "es": "Que tú historias serás.",
    "tr": "That you will become stories."
  },
  {
    "es": "Que tú en cuentos vendrás.",
    "tr": "That you will return in tales."
  }
]